     * Hint: This problem is similar to finding a specific node in a graph. As stated in the README, one of the ways you
     * could approach this is to use Breadth-First Search.
     * </p>
     *
     * @return {@code true} if a path exists, else {@code false}.
     */
    public boolean checkPath() {
        Set<Coordinate> visited = new HashSet<>();
        Queue<Coordinate> queue = new LinkedList<>();
        queue.add(sourceCell.coord);
        visited.add(sourceCell.coord);

        while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
            Coordinate current = queue.poll();
            if (current.equals(sinkCell.coord)) {
                return true;
            }

            Cell cell = cells[current.row][current.col];
            if (cell instanceof FillableCell) {
                FillableCell fillableCell = (FillableCell) cell;
                fillableCell.getPipe().ifPresent(pipe -> {
                    for (Direction dir : pipe.getConnections()) {
                        Coordinate newCoord = current.add(dir.getOffset());
                        if (isValidCoordinate(newCoord) && !visited.contains(newCoord)) {
                            Cell adjacentCell = cells[newCoord.row][newCoord.col];
                            if (adjacentCell instanceof FillableCell) {
                                FillableCell adjacentFillableCell = (FillableCell) adjacentCell;
                                adjacentFillableCell.getPipe().ifPresent(adjacentPipe -> {
                                    if (Arrays.asList(adjacentPipe.getConnections()).contains(dir.getOpposite())) {
                                        queue.add(newCoord);
                                        visited.add(newCoord);
                                    }
                                });
                            } else if (adjacentCell instanceof TerminationCell) {
                                TerminationCell terminationCell = (TerminationCell) adjacentCell;
                                if (terminationCell.pointingTo == dir.getOpposite()) {
                                    queue.add(newCoord);
                                    visited.add(newCoord);
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                });
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

    /**
     * <p>
     * Hint: From the README: {@code The game is lost when a round ends and no pipes are filled during the round.} Is
     * there a way to check whether pipes are filled during a round?
     * </p>
     *
     * @return {@code true} if the game is lost.
     */
    public boolean hasLost() {
        return filledTiles.size() == prevFilledTiles;
    }

    private boolean isValidCoordinate(Coordinate coord) {
        return coord.row >= 0 && coord.row < rows && coord.col >= 0 && coord.col < cols;
    }
}
